@node reg "Register and support shareware"
@{fg shine}
    How to "register" and why?
@{fg text}
    At this stage of development, this software is considered to be
    FreeWare. This means that anyone may use it without any restrictions.

@{fg shine}
    So why "register"?
@{fg text}
    By registering you first of all give me feed-back that A-Start is
    a useful program, thus inspiring me to finish the 1.0 version more
    quickly. The 1.0 version of A-Start will be released as shareware.

    The fact is that I will continue developing A-Start no matter how
    many users register or send me comments.  I think it is a useful
    piece of software, and that it should be developed further into new
    dimensions.  And why not support a programmer who's software you use?
    I haven't slept for many weeks to give you the pleasure of using this
    program, now its you're time to do something for me ;).
@{fg shine}
    Why do I write "register" in quotation marks?
@{fg text}
    At this stage you cannot register, due to the freeware status of the
    program).  You can only support me.  BUT:  All users who support me
    at this stage will be treated as registered users of future A-Start
    releases.

    To "register": send US$13/16DM/50FMK, any along with a letter, to:
@{fg shine}
	  Tuomas Artman
	  Pððrynðpolku 3
	  02710 Espoo
	  Finland
@{fg text}
    The letter should contain the following information:
@{fg shine}
	  Name
	  City
	  Country
	  Email address

@{fg text}
    If you do not have an email-address, you have to include your street
    address and zipcode, and a formatted disk!

    You will receive your keyfile when the 1.0 Version of A-Start is ready.


  @{" Back to main " LINK main}
@endnode

@node future "What is to come?"
@{fg shine}
  Future versions of A-Start:
@{fg text}
    A-Start is right now going through serious development and many things
    WILL change and be included in future versions:

    - It will be possible to enter "drawers" into the proglist and file-
    list-windows.  This will give you another way to organize your files
    and projects (for example, put all gfx programs into a proglist/gfx
    directory, and all text editors into proglist/text).

    - The command window is UGLY. This will change in future versions.

    - All graphics will be redrawn, and many, many more will be included.
    The idea is to have a GUI with nice and intuitive graphics everywhere.

    - The "slide" method of the FileWindows is not very good.  In future
    versions the user may choose if he wants to use the current method,
    or a scroll bar on the left (or right) side of the window.

    - Requesters will be replaced by my own reqesters. They will have lots of
    nice graphics and other neat stuff.

    - The whole program will be speeded up (especially opening and closing
    windows).

    - Many more file-types will be supported. If you have a file type that
    you want included, please e-mail me!

    - Currently the program is unstable and there are many known bugs.
    All these will be fixed.  Please report bugs as you encounter them!

    - The program uses a lot of CPU time when the start-button has been
    pressed.  Although this should not be a problem for most users, it will
    be changed to use less processor cycles in the future.

    - Not only a lot of neat graphics will be added, but also music and
    sound-effects. Of course with full ability to customize.

    - Lowmem/highmem option is not present yet.  In future versions it will
    be possible to keep A-Start memory consumption low, with an increase of
    disk activity.  All graphics are flushed from memory when not needed.

    - Some serious bug hunting and subsequent extermination will be done.

    - Does anyone know how to open these wb drawer windows with icons?

    Yes, there is a lot to do, and I really need your help!
    Please read the @{"Register" LINK reg} and the @{"Programmers" LINK programmers} pages!


  @{" Back to main " LINK main}
@endnode
@node quit "How to quit?"
@{fg shine}
  How to quit A-Start:
@{fg text}
    If you want to quit A-Start you first have to activate one of A-Starts
    windows (for example by pressing one of A-Starts buttons) and then press
    the right mouse-button.  A-Start will clean up and terminate.

    If you just want to close the file windows, simply click somewhere on
    your workbench.  Note that this does not work if you have opened the
    UserProgs or the FileList window.  In that case just click the button
    at the bottom left marked "Amiga", and all windows will be closed.


  @{" Back to main " LINK main}

@endnode

@node new "New features of A-Start"


------------------------------------
early March 96 - A-Start v0.75 ready
------------------------------------
New features:

    -A-StartWBS-program added to the package. With it you can start
    A-Start on every bootup from your WBStartup-drawer.

    -THE FILELIST-WINDOW IS NOW IN USE! Read the usage-section to find
    out, how to use it...

    -Possibility to choose the look of the gadget, appearing below the
    mouse-pointer. Use A-Start prefs to configure it.

    -A-StartPrefs rewritten. The v0.75 A-StartPrefs-program does NOT
    support the v0.52 Env-file, but all newer versions of A-Start will
    be backward-compatible.

    -Possibility to define your prefs-drawer in case you do not put your
    pref-files into 'Sys:Prefs/'.

    -You may now choose if A-Start closes its windows after viewing a pic,
    reading a text..., or if the windows should remain opened.

    -Support for Mod and Med- MusicDataFiles and Sound-effects.

    -Bugfixing. A-Start SHOULD work now better on 3.1 platforms.


---------------------------------------------
late February 96 - A-Start v0.52 hits the net.
---------------------------------------------









